{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This backend supports Linux, macOS and Windows (maybe?), but its support for non-Linux platforms is significantly worse than ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"â€˜s (due to underlying Gtk 3 issues). Even on Linux, itâ€™s recommended to use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" over Gtk3Backend where possible.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Non-Linux Gtk3Backend support is not a priority of this backend, and should only be used during development (e.g. to test your Linux UI natively on a Mac). There are multiple better choices of backend available on each non-Linux platform.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Warning","style":"warning","type":"aside"},{"anchor":"System-dependencies","text":"System dependencies","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before you can use Gtk3Backend you must install the required system dependencies for your platform.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Linux","text":"Linux","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"code":["sudo apt install libgtk-3-dev"],"syntax":"sh","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 1: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"installing Gtk 3 dev on an apt-based Linux distro"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you are on a non-apt distro and the Gtk3Backend requirements end up differing significantly from the requirements stated above, please open a GitHub issue or PR so that we can improve the documentation.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"macOS","text":"macOS","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"code":["brew install pkg-config